273
00:21:29,260 --> 00:21:30,270
Is that so?

274
00:21:30,270 --> 00:21:31,920
That is not true.

275
00:21:31,920 --> 00:21:33,200
What do you mean it's not true?

276
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:37,450
When you were a prosecution trainee,
your mentor gave you low scores.

277
00:21:37,450 --> 00:21:40,460
You filed a complaint against him for
sexual harassment as revenge.

278
00:21:40,460 --> 00:21:42,220
That's it.

279
00:21:42,220 --> 00:21:43,730
Do you admit that?

280
00:21:43,730 --> 00:21:45,180
I cannot admit it.

281
00:21:45,180 --> 00:21:46,920
Then we will fight in court.

282
00:21:48,480 --> 00:21:50,450
Do you have anything else to say?

283
00:21:50,450 --> 00:21:53,130
I don't think she will be accepted
into the trial research institute,

284
00:21:53,130 --> 00:21:54,740
but even if she is,

285
00:21:54,740 --> 00:21:56,810
if she is indicted, she will be kicked out.

286
00:21:56,810 --> 00:22:00,540
I pity her future, so I will only say five words.

287
00:22:00,540 --> 00:22:03,120
I will think about whether
I want to let her off easy.

288
00:22:03,120 --> 00:22:05,100
What are the five words?

289
00:22:08,630 --> 00:22:14,120
Please, save, my, life, sir.

290
00:22:16,990 --> 00:22:19,550
Are you saying if she apologizes,
you will let her off easy?

291
00:22:21,610 --> 00:22:23,570
Get on your knees and apologize.

292
00:22:23,570 --> 00:22:26,270
You want to be unemployed after graduating from law school?

293
00:22:26,270 --> 00:22:28,720
You need to pay your bills.

294
00:22:40,300 --> 00:22:42,410
I...

295
00:22:42,410 --> 00:22:45,410
only testified the truth.

296
00:22:47,420 --> 00:22:50,550
Also, because of the
"innocent until proven guilty" rule,

297
00:22:50,550 --> 00:22:55,130
an indictment is not sufficient
reason for dismissal.

298
00:22:55,130 --> 00:22:57,510
You don't have to...

299
00:22:57,510 --> 00:22:59,780
pretend like you care about my future.

300
00:22:59,780 --> 00:23:02,430
Are you throwing out a challenge right now

301
00:23:02,430 --> 00:23:04,170
to a prosecutor of South Korea?

302
00:23:04,170 --> 00:23:07,400
A challenge would be for a champion.

303
00:23:07,400 --> 00:23:10,020
Is a prosecutor our society's champion?

304
00:23:11,270 --> 00:23:14,090
You are out of your mind.

305
00:23:14,090 --> 00:23:16,220
What makes you so arrogant?

306
00:23:18,560 --> 00:23:20,050
Justice.

307
00:23:53,070 --> 00:23:58,420
He touched my thigh. When I attacked him,
you gave me a thumbs up.

308
00:23:58,420 --> 00:24:00,260
So what do you mean you didn't see it?

309
00:24:00,260 --> 00:24:01,970
I didn't say I didn't see it.

310
00:24:01,970 --> 00:24:03,470
Then you saw it.

311
00:24:03,470 --> 00:24:05,240
I told you already.

312
00:24:05,240 --> 00:24:07,060
I don't know.

313
00:24:07,060 --> 00:24:09,130
When you say you don't know,

314
00:24:09,130 --> 00:24:12,540
do you mean you saw it or you didn't?

315
00:24:12,540 --> 00:24:14,290
Like I said.

316
00:24:14,290 --> 00:24:16,170
I don't know.

317
00:24:16,170 --> 00:24:17,730
Meaning, I don't know.

318
00:24:17,730 --> 00:24:19,220
Madame.

319
00:24:19,220 --> 00:24:22,470
As a woman, I understand your situation.

320
00:24:22,470 --> 00:24:24,760
But I still don't know.

321
00:24:24,760 --> 00:24:27,290
I might not know because I didn't see it,

322
00:24:27,290 --> 00:24:30,560
or I might have seen it, but not
know if it was harassment.

323
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:33,710
You saw it, right?

324
00:24:33,710 --> 00:24:35,460
Do you have a boyfriend?

325
00:24:36,700 --> 00:24:38,500
I have a great guy for you.

326
00:24:38,500 --> 00:24:41,250
He's in business. Want to meet him?

327
00:24:44,610 --> 00:24:48,070
My life is on the line, madame.

328
00:24:48,070 --> 00:24:50,800
Can I give you advice as an unni?

329
00:24:52,010 --> 00:24:56,000
Don't put your life on the line for anything.

330
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:58,450
Then your life will just be
more burdensome.

331
00:25:06,070 --> 00:25:07,370
Section Leader!

332
00:25:23,370 --> 00:25:24,960
Song So Eun...

333
00:25:26,140 --> 00:25:29,630
was interrogated by prosecution recently.

334
00:25:29,630 --> 00:25:31,690
Our Trainee Song?

335
00:25:31,690 --> 00:25:33,510
Please keep it a secret.

336
00:25:33,510 --> 00:25:35,280
Of course, but...

337
00:25:35,280 --> 00:25:38,670
What happened? She would never do
something to warrant that.

338
00:25:38,670 --> 00:25:41,000
Could you get the word on the street?

339
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:44,170
How she got involved, how it's progressing?

340
00:25:44,170 --> 00:25:45,980
Everything that might be helpful.

341
00:25:45,980 --> 00:25:49,730
That won't be too difficult,
but you called me up here.

342
00:25:49,730 --> 00:25:53,130
Your Honor, your connections in
this field are all gone, right?

343
00:25:53,130 --> 00:25:57,210
What are you talking about?
Connections are how I live.

344
00:25:57,210 --> 00:25:59,060
I heard about it.

345
00:25:59,060 --> 00:26:01,250
You've been looking for a
law professor position,

346
00:26:01,250 --> 00:26:03,380
but no interview has led
to something yet.

347
00:26:05,760 --> 00:26:08,550
That bastard Lee Ho Sung still hasn't
come to his senses after being arrested.

348
00:26:08,550 --> 00:26:13,380
He's threatening to cancel every scholarship
his company funds if you get a professorship.

349
00:26:13,380 --> 00:26:15,310
The schools should not fall for that.

350
00:26:15,310 --> 00:26:18,020
They're just desperate for corporate support.

351
00:26:20,140 --> 00:26:21,480
That...

352
00:26:21,480 --> 00:26:23,380
Cheer up.

353
00:26:23,380 --> 00:26:25,380
It's unusual that you didn't become a lawyer

354
00:26:25,380 --> 00:26:27,170
and also unusual you want to be a professor,

355
00:26:27,170 --> 00:26:31,160
but you've always done well
in unusual situations.

356
00:26:33,110 --> 00:26:35,620
Don't worry too much about Trainee Song.

357
00:26:35,620 --> 00:26:37,740
I heard she requested to be a trial researcher.

358
00:26:37,740 --> 00:26:41,660
It's competitive, but once she gets it,
no one can touch her.

359
00:26:41,660 --> 00:26:43,400
Yes.

360
00:26:43,400 --> 00:26:45,240
She has to get it.

361
00:26:45,240 --> 00:26:46,630
She will.

362
00:26:46,630 --> 00:26:50,780
So Your Honor, whatever you do, do it well.

363
00:26:50,780 --> 00:26:53,280
Trainee Song really trusted
and looked up to you.

364
00:26:58,750 --> 00:27:00,560
Go ahead, Your Honor.

365
00:27:02,030 --> 00:27:03,700
Not that.

366
00:27:03,700 --> 00:27:11,240
♫ I tried revealing my inner thoughts ♫

367
00:27:11,240 --> 00:27:20,680
♫ No one, nothing has
ever changed for me ♫

368
00:27:20,680 --> 00:27:29,960
♫ I wished it would pass me, I wished
